A quick-thinking Canadian woman has been diagnosed with a stroke after she filmed herself suffering the symptoms - after doctors previously insisted she was simply stressed.

Stacey Yepes, 49, from Thornhill, Ontario, recognized her numbness and partial facial paralysis as signs of having a stroke, so she went to the ER - but doctors sent her away with advice on how to manage stress.

'They told me I needed 
to learn how to manage my stress,' she told CNN. 'I just laughed to myself and thought, "This is not stress". I couldnt believe that was the diagnosis they came 
up with.'

