She had an MRI scan and the stroke team identified a small injury.

They determined that her mini strokes were caused by a buildup of plaque in her arteries, and a blood clot then formed on the plaque, blocking an artery leading to her brain.

Although she only suffered temporary mini strokes, they are a sign that a full-blown stroke could be around the corner.

